"n.自然的增加；增加物 【英】 n.自然的增加(growth in size by accumulation)；增加物( addition) 【考】 反义词：reduction in substance caused by erosion(由侵蚀引起 的物质减少) 【记】 ac+cret(增加)+ion 【同】 adj. accretive n. 自然的增加(因外部的添加, 连接而生长并在体积上逐渐增大的过程); 增加物(为促使生长的外部添加物) = addition 【例】accretion of population 人口增加 【根】ac一再, cret增加, 升起－自然的增加 【反】reduction in substance caused by erosion(由侵蚀引起的物质减少) 【记】ac+cret(增加)+ion,见accrue； accretion (n.)  1610s, from Latin accretionem (nominative accretio) ""an increasing, a growing larger"" (as of the waxing moon), noun of action from past participle stem of accrescere, from ad- ""to"" (see ad-) + crescere ""grow"" (see crescent)."
